                                                                        <p>14. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from certain individuals of his people in a marfu ’ manner from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “When you are about to sleep say, ‘O Lord, if You holdback my soul from returning to my body, have mercy on it and if You will allow it to return, please protect it. ’” </p>
